<vocabulary>
- valid refund request: a request whose amount_cents is greater than 0 and not greater than the captured payment amount
- duplicate refund: a request whose tenant ID and idempotency key match a previously accepted refund request
</vocabulary>

<contract_rules>
R1 - Reject zero refund
When a refund request has amount_cents equal to 0,
the service MUST return HTTP 400 and MUST NOT call provider_client.

R2 - Reject duplicate refund
When a request is a duplicate refund,
the service MUST return HTTP 409 and MUST NOT write a new refund record.

R3 - Emit accepted event
When a valid refund request is accepted,
the service MUST return HTTP 201 and MUST emit refund.accepted.
</contract_rules>
